    hide eli_navarro
    hide maya_reyes

    scene bg ch12_e67f19_5 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The tide sighs; distant cheering fades into the background like the last wave of a passing storm]
    "You close your eyes for a heartbeat and name the people who will keep you accountable, who will make the accord live: Tomas, Rosa, Asha, the neighbors—each a knot in the scaffold. You make a private"
    "vow: to show up, to keep talking, to guard the legal teeth in the agreement like a patient wolf."
    "You open your eyes. Eli's face is a map of devotion and mischief; he lifts his brow, wordless. You answer with a small, steady nod."
    "The town breathes around you — a living thing stitched together by promises and arguments and small mercies. The hybrid accord is fragile and mighty at once. It will not fix everything. It will, however, buy"
    "habitats space, secure funding for living modules, and create the legal room for the community to fight evacuation and displacement on their own terms."
    "You press your palm harder into the basalt, feeling the cool give of stone and sea. The finality of the day's work settles like a tide-line on your skin: a clear mark of where you've been and where you'll have to keep going."
    "You are tired. You are alive."
